{"lemma":"حِطَّةٍ","slug":"حِطَّةٍ","root":"ح.ط.ط","root_slug":"ح-ط-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ط-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حِطَّة","root":"حطط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8350","n8354"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alleviation; relief"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"debasement; insult"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"demotion"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8350","headword_ar":"حَطَّهُ","root":"HT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~N","text_ar":"حَطٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put it down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDaEahu","text_ar":"وَضَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anozalahu","text_ar":"اَنْزَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a high to a lower place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) namely a load, or any other thing from a back; (TA;) a camel's saddle, (S, Msb, TA,) or other thing; (Msb;) a horse's saddle; and a bow; (S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtT~hu","text_ar":"احتطّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a AlA^aHomaAla Eani","text_ar":"حَطَّ الاَحْمَالَ عَنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~awaAb~i","text_ar":"الدَّوَابِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put down the loads from the beasts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a Eanohu wizorahu","text_ar":"حَطَّ عَنْهُ وِزْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put down from him his heavy burden:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his heavy burden of sin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, * K, * TA:) if a real load be intended, this is proper; but if an ideal thing, it is tropical; (TA;) [as when you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuT~a Ean~aA *unuwbanaA","text_ar":"حُطَّ عَنَّا ذُنُوبَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put Thou down from us"},{"kind":"text","text":"the burden of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"our sins"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a raHolahu","text_ar":"حَطَّ رَحْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put down his camel's saddle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he stayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a","text_ar":"حَطَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, [elliptically,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alighted and abode;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY makaAnK","text_ar":"فِى مَكَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw it down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely a thing. (TA.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He paid it down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely money.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to descend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to go down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"downwards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"down a declivity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from above to below."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) Imra-el-Keys says, [describing a horse in motion,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kajulomuwdi SaxorK HaT~ahu Als~ayolu mino Eali"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like a mass of rock which the torrent has made to descend from above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lowered him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"degraded him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a mina Alv~amani ka*aA","text_ar":"حَطَّ مِنَ الثَّمَنِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abated of the price so much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoqaTa","text_ar":"اَسْقَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a minohu","text_ar":"حَطَّ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTiyTapF waAfiyapF","text_ar":"حَطِيطَةً وَافِيَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a large abatement of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTiyTapN","text_ar":"حَطِيطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTaTotu mina Ald~ayoni","text_ar":"حَطَطْتُ مِنَ الدَّيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I abated"},{"kind":"text","text":"[somewhat]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the debt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [See also 10.] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~ahu","text_ar":"حَطَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~ahu","text_ar":"حَتَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": as in a trad. where it is said of Mohammad, that he sat by a dry branch of a tree,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqaAla biyadihi wa HaT~a waraqahaA","text_ar":"فَقَالَ بِيَدِهِ وَ حَطَّ وَرَقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he made a sign with his hand, and removed its leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered its leaves."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA.) And so in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ubodu yuHaT~u Eani All~abani","text_ar":"الزُّبْدُ يُحَطُّ عَنِ اللَّبَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The froth is removed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skimmed off, from the milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a Als~iEoru","text_ar":"حَطَّ السِّعْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, TA, [but I think it more probable that the aor. is"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy, like as some say of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaT~a","text_ar":"قَطَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, accord. to Sh, signifies the same, or nearly so, but accord. to others, the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a","text_ar":"حَطَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~N","text_ar":"حَطٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuTuwTN","text_ar":"حُطُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The price was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheap;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it abated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qT","text_ar":"قط"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnHT~","text_ar":"انحطّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Fr ubi suprà, S, * TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a AlbaEiyru","text_ar":"حَطَّ البَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alsayori","text_ar":"فِى السَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiTaATN","text_ar":"حِطَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel bore upon his nose-rein"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards one side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in going;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnHT~","text_ar":"انحطّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or, accord. to AA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnHT~t Aln~aAqapu fiY sayorihaA","text_ar":"انحطّت النَّاقَةُ فِى سَيْرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the she-camel was quick in her pace;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~at","text_ar":"حَطَّت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiTaATN","text_ar":"حِطَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement running."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [From what next follows, it seems that the verb in this sense is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEila","text_ar":"فَعِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  The poet 'Amr-Ibn-El-Ahtam uses the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~iY fiY hawaAYa","text_ar":"حَطِّى فِى هَوَاىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rest thou upon my love, and incline my way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHaT~ato A_ilaY Al$~aAb~i","text_ar":"فَحَطَّتْ اـِلَى الشَّابِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And she inclined with her heart towards the youth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a fiY EiroDi fulaAnK","text_ar":"حَطَّ فِى عِرْضِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He launched forth into,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressed on in, the reviling of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a fiY AlT~aEaAmi","text_ar":"حَطَّ فِى الطَّعَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate the food;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HT~T","text_ar":"حطّط","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoTiyTN","text_ar":"تَحْطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ate much of the food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~a Aljiloda","text_ar":"حَطَّ الجِلْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~N","text_ar":"حَطٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He polished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smoothed, the skin;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decorated, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruled it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made lines upon it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHaT~","text_ar":"مِحَطّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","K","L","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n8354","headword_ar":"حِطَّةٌ","root":"HT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A petition for the putting down of a heavy burden from one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the heavy burden of sin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or merely"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a putting down thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstHT~hu wizorahu","text_ar":"استحطّهُ وِزْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained above; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiT~iyTaY","text_ar":"حِطِّيطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) It is said in the Kur [ii. 55, and vii. 161],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa quwluwA HiT~apN","text_ar":"وَ قُولُوا حِطَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e. they were told to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiT~apN","text_ar":"حِطَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the purpose of asking thereby for the putting down of their heavy burdens from them, and they should be put down from them: (Ibn-Isráeel, TA:) the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And say ye, Put Thou down from us our heavy burdens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"our sins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-' Arafeh, K:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and say ye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Our petition is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiT~apN","text_ar":"حِطَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that Thou wouldest put down from us our sins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is- hák, K:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiT~ap","text_ar":"حِطَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a word which the children of Israel were commanded to say; and if they said it, their heavy burdens, or sins, were put down: (S, TA:) accord. to IAar, it is the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A_il`ha A_il~aA A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"لَا اـِلٰهَ اـِلَّا ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forgiveness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I' Ab:) or our affair is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an alighting and abiding"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this town: (Bd in ii. 55:) and there is another reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa quwluwA HiT~apF","text_ar":"وَ قُولُوا حِطَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is explained in two ways; either by making the verb to govern the noun, as though he had said,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and say ye a saying which shall put down from you your heavy burdens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sins;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or by making the noun to be in the accus. case as an inf. n. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplicating"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"petitioning"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that God may put down from you your heavy burdens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sins"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AuHoTuTi A@ll~ahum~a A^awozaAranaA HiT~apF","text_ar":"اُحْطُطِ ا@للَّهُمَّ اَوْزَارَنَا حِطَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) but they changed this saying, (Fr, Sgh, K,) using for it a Nabathean expression; (Fr, TA;) saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiT~iY sumohaAvFA","text_ar":"هِطِّى سُمْهَاثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ” red wheat, “ (Sgh, K,) accord. to Es-Suddee and Mujáhid; or, accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinoTapF $umoqaAyaA","text_ar":"حِنْطَةً شُمْقَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ” good wheat. “ (Sgh, TA.) You say also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA^alahu AlHiT~iyTaY","text_ar":"سَاَلَهُ الحِطِّيطَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHiT~apa","text_ar":"الحِطَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He asked of him the putting down of his heavy burden from him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his sin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it is said in a trad., that when God tries a person with a trial in his body,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa lahu HiT~apN","text_ar":"هُوَ لَهُ حِطَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is to him a mode of putting down from him his sins."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHiT~apu","text_ar":"الحِطَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of the month of Ramadán,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Gospel, or some other book: (Az, K, * TA:) because it puts down somewhat of the sin of him who observes the fast thereof. (Az, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A decrease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of diminution, in respect of rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHuTuTu","text_ar":"الحُطُطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is its pl., (TA,) is explained as signifying, (K, TA,) on the authority of IAar, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAkibu","text_ar":"مَرَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ifali","text_ar":"السِّفَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAtibu Als~ifali","text_ar":"مَرَاتِبُ السِّفَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) the latter [meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ranks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stations, of the lowest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest, of mankind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is the right reading, as verified by Az. (TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":593}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Fr","Sgh","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}